tractions-splice-spp-360x240/09/2e/42/9c.jpg\", \"description\": null, \"primaryCategory\": \"Luxury Tours\"}, {\"url\": \"https://www.tripadvisor.com/Commerce?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.viator.com%2Ftours%2FAlbuquerque%2FGuided-Bicycle-Nature-Tour-of-Albuquerque-Daily%2Fd28131-170615P1%3Feap%3Dtripadvisor-main-11383%26aid%3Dtripen1&partnerKey=1&urlKey=b7ed3a1a7a044bcf0&logme=true&uidparam=refid&attrc=true&Provider=Viator&area=viator_multi&slot=5&cnt=1&geo=144329&clt=TD&from=api&nt=true\", \"price\": \"$125.00\", \"roundedUpPrice\": \"$125\", \"offerType\": null, \"title\": \"Guided Bicycle Nature Tour of Albuquerque - Daily\", \"productCode\": \"170615P1\", \"partner\": \"Viator\", \"imageUrl\": \"https://media.tacdn.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-360x240/10/76/9e/17.jpg\", \"description\": null, \"primaryCategory\": \"Historical & Heritage Tours\"}]}", subtype: ["Neighborhoods", "Historic Walking Areas"], ratingHistogram: "{\"count1\": 46, \"count2\": 178, \"count3\": 830, \"count4\": 1904, \"count5\": 2438}", location_contains_city: "True", id: "144329", longitude: "-106.66946", rankingPosition: "23.0", address: "N Plaza St NW, Albuquerque, NM 87104", neighborhoodLocations: "[{\"id\": \"20483743\", \"name\": \"West Old Town\"}]", rankingString: "#23 of 383 things to do in Albuquerque", City: "Albuquerque", localName: "Albuquerque Old Town", State: "New Mexico", webUrl: "https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g60933-d144329-Reviews-Albuquerque_Old_Town-Albuquerque_New_Mexico.html", localAddress: "N Plaza St NW, 87104", rankingDenominator: "383.0", name: "Albuquerque Old Town", locationString: "Albuquerque, New Mexico", subcategories: ["Sights & Landmarks", "Other"], rawRanking: "3.762952566", node_key: "Attraction::144329", source_kind: "mini_kg" };
MERGE (n:Attraction {node_key: "Attraction::2242229"})
SET n += { nearestMetroStations: [], localLangCode: "en-US", numberOfReviews: "206", latitude: "35.103397", rating: "5.0", description: "New Mexico Steam Locomotive & Railroad Historical Society, an all-volunteer, 501(c)3 non-profit, is preserving New Mexico's railway history. After over 20 years of effort, the society's volunteers have thoroughly restored the former Atchison Topeka & Santa Fe (AT&SF) No. 2926, a 4-8-4 “Northern,” built in 1944. The Santa Fe 2926 locomotive is the only operating 2900-class in the United States, and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places and recognized by the state's legislature as the Official Steam Locomotive of New Mexico. Come to 1833 8th St NW in Albuquerque to experience this magnificent piece of history! The NMSL&RHS restoration site is open to the public for free 'hard hat' tours (weather permitting) Wednesday and Saturday from 9:00 AM to 2:00 PM. Group tours can be arranged on any day by appointment (505-246-2926). Parking is free and donations are important to keep the restoration moving forward. Merchandise is available for purchase from the gift shop.", visit_duration: "3.0", addressObj: "{\"street1\": \"1833 8th St NW\", \"street2\": \"Only a few blocks South of I-40 on 8th St at the railroad tracks\", \"city\": \"Albuquerque\", \"state\": \"NM\", \"country\": \"United States\", \"postalcode\": \"87102-1210\"}", subtype: ["Specialty Museums", "Points of Interest & Landmarks"], ratingHistogram: "{\"count1\": 0, \"count2\": 1, \"count3\": 2, \"count4\": 23, \"count5\": 180}", location_contains_city: "True", id: "2242229", longitude: "-106.65472", website: "http://2926.us", rankingPosition: "1.0", address: "1833 8th St NW Only a few blocks South of I-40 on 8th St at the railroad tracks, Albuquerque, NM 87102-1210", neighborhoodLocations: "[{\"id\": \"21001905\", \"name\": \"Raynolds Addition\"}]", rankingString: "#1 of 383 things to do in Albuquerque", City: "Albuquerque", localName: "New Mexico Steam Locomotive and Railroad Historical Society", State: "New Mexico", webUrl: "https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g60933-d2242229-Reviews-New_Mexico_Steam_Locomotive_and_Railroad_Historical_Society-Albuquerque_New_Mexico.html", localAddress: "1833 8th St NW, Only a few blocks South of I-40 on 8th St at the railroad tracks, 87102-1210", rankingDenominator: "383.0", name: "New Mexico Steam Locomotive and Railroad Historical Society", locationString: "Albuquerque, New Mexico", subcategories: ["Sights & Landmarks", "Museums"], rawRanking: "4.306842327", node_key: "Attraction::2242229", source_kind: "mini_kg" };
